1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:05,080
♪ Inside the state a city is built ♪

2
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:10,190
♪ Where a benevolent emperor resides ♪

3
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:15,330
♪ Court officials are brave and able ♪

4
00:00:15,330 --> 00:00:22,750
♪ The empress is fair ♪

5
00:00:25,580 --> 00:00:30,710
♪ Princes died too young to ascend the throne ♪

6
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:35,570
♪ Princesses are spoiled and fragile ♪

7
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:40,270
♪ Commoners are also the emperor’s children ♪

8
00:00:40,830 --> 00:00:49,630
♪ All are living peacefully ♪

9
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:54,280
♪ Wish I could live a day for myself ♪

10
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,380
♪ Follow my heart and ethics without distractions ♪

11
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:03,400
♪ To be a good husband ♪

12
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,970
♪ To be a caring father ♪

13
00:01:06,460 --> 00:01:10,110
♪ We were close when we first met ♪

14
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:14,710
♪ I hope I can control my desires ♪

15
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:20,060
♪ To be a worriless emperor and father ♪

16
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,860
♪ Prudence tops all virtues ♪

17
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,480
♪ People build the state ♪

18
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:30,020
= Held in the Lonely Castle =
♪ May the world be peaceful ♪

19
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:33,020
= Episode 56 =

20
00:01:33,020 --> 00:01:36,980
= The Hall of Happiness and Tranquility =

21
00:01:58,580 --> 00:01:59,780
Scholar Feng, you may leave.

22
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:05,380
Noble Consort Zhang died early.

23
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:09,620
His Majesty is too sorrowful.

24
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:13,820
I agree to title her after her death, too.

25
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:17,580
I work for the imperial court.

26
00:02:19,260 --> 00:02:20,220
I’m not objecting,

27
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:22,700
to complain for you, Your Highness,

28
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:26,180
but to follow the etiquettes of our nation.

29
00:02:27,860 --> 00:02:29,060
This is my obligation.

30
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,140
As an official,

31
00:02:34,380 --> 00:02:35,900
are you only obligated to

32
00:02:36,820 --> 00:02:37,820
defend the etiquettes meticulously?

33
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:41,540
You’re a principal graduate.

34
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:45,260
You must be more knowledgeable than me.

35
00:02:47,420 --> 00:02:50,020
I didn’t dare to discuss with you

36
00:02:50,180 --> 00:02:53,140
on imperial rules or etiquettes.

37
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:57,180
I just want to say something

38
00:02:57,180 --> 00:02:58,380
Mr. Fan Zhongyan said

39
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:01,260
when he was alive.

40
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:04,100
Mr. Fan?

41
00:03:05,660 --> 00:03:06,580
I heard

42
00:03:07,740 --> 00:03:09,340
when you were young,

43
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:11,180
you were instructed by Mr. Fan.

44
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:15,580
I first met Mr. Fan

45
00:03:17,380 --> 00:03:18,980
outside the gate of Shangqiu Academy.

46
00:03:21,460 --> 00:03:24,940
Because he was in an old robe,

47
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:27,940
the proctor and a group of students

48
00:03:27,940 --> 00:03:31,020
laughed at him for breach of etiquette.

49
00:03:33,140 --> 00:03:34,660
When I saw that,

50
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:36,660
I suddenly opposed

51
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,380
such etiquettes.

52
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:44,380
They were so young that they talked ravings.

53
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,380
But Mr. Fan said

54
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:53,420
etiquette starts from respect
and ends with benevolence.

55
00:03:55,260 --> 00:03:59,540
Etiquette starts from respect
and ends with benevolence?

56
00:04:01,140 --> 00:04:01,820
Title her after her death.

57
00:04:02,540 --> 00:04:04,140
When I can accept it

58
00:04:04,140 --> 00:04:05,220
as the alive empress,

59
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:08,060
will it really influence imperial policies

60
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:09,780
or the peace of people?

61
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:14,020
Human beings are emotional.

62
00:04:14,940 --> 00:04:15,820
I don’t think

63
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,900
ancestors set up rules or etiquettes

64
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:21,380
to destroy human feelings,

65
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:26,180
but to defend them.

66
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:08,380
Princess.

67
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:10,180
Miss Cao just came to the palace

68
00:06:10,180 --> 00:06:11,340
with Mrs. Cao,

69
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:13,220
and she returned the umbrella for Mr. Cao Ping.

70
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:15,580
It’s just an umbrella.

71
00:06:16,020 --> 00:06:16,940
No need to return it.

72
00:06:17,860 --> 00:06:19,100
But she said

73
00:06:19,380 --> 00:06:20,780
Mr. Cao Ping urged again and again that

74
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:21,820
you didn’t

75
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:22,940
give the umbrella to him.

76
00:06:23,420 --> 00:06:24,700
He just borrowed it.

77
00:06:24,740 --> 00:06:25,660
He must return it.

78
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:27,500
Miss Cao also said

79
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:29,500
her brother was always careless.

80
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:30,460
He often breaks things

81
00:06:30,460 --> 00:06:31,580
that he has borrowed.

82
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:33,700
Why don’t you check

83
00:06:34,260 --> 00:06:36,660
if the umbrella is in good condition.

84
00:06:55,460 --> 00:06:59,060
Trees were bathed in the rays of the setting sun.

85
00:07:00,860 --> 00:07:04,140
I went boating and played music.

86
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:08,300
= Xiao Ye’er =
You wore a perfect makeup.

87
00:07:09,860 --> 00:07:11,060
Your dress was fluttering.

88
00:07:12,460 --> 00:07:15,220
You listened to my perfect songs.

89
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:18,940
When the sun set, the spring ended.

90
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:22,380
It was hard to keep you.

91
00:07:23,340 --> 00:07:26,500
I hated it when we met in the palace,

92
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:29,100
you said nothing to me.

93
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:34,540
Falling flowers wafted in autumn rains.

94
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,700
Princess, you and Mr. Cao

95
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:41,340
met beside the lake.

96
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:42,860
He was singing songs.

97
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,820
In the last few sentences, he felt sad.

98
00:07:46,260 --> 00:07:47,780
During the banquets these years,

99
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:49,260
you didn’t talk to him.

100
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:54,580
Yeah.

101
00:07:56,580 --> 00:07:57,900
Even father can’t

102
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:58,940
let go of his love.

103
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:03,100
Why must I chain myself

104
00:08:04,660 --> 00:08:06,500
to that rotten wood for the rest of my life?

105
00:08:27,220 --> 00:08:28,060
Mr. Wang.

106
00:08:29,540 --> 00:08:30,460
Please come in.

107
00:08:35,980 --> 00:08:38,820
= Wang Gongchen, courtesy name Junkuang =

108
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:40,220
The first draft has been completed.

109
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:41,900
You had hard work.

110
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:53,380
This decree is to honor dead consort
as the Empress,

111
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:58,140
for the contributions she made before dying.

112
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:02,340
Dead Empress Zhang was gentle and obedient,

113
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:04,340
but died in the prime of life.

114
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,220
Do you think

115
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:14,380
I only flatter His Majesty?

116
00:09:23,100 --> 00:09:24,420
You’re a smart man, Mr. Wang.

117
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:26,820
You can see through the future politics.

118
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:29,140
Noble Consort Zhang died.

119
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:31,260
Zhang Yaozuo is neither talented nor capable.

120
00:09:31,860 --> 00:09:34,260
His Majesty always respects Her Highness.

121
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:36,900
Her Highness has the Thirteenth Prince as her son.

122
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:39,500
She will be the Empress Dowager.

123
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:43,140
If you strive for Noble Consort Zhang,

124
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:45,300
you’ll get nothing useful

125
00:09:45,420 --> 00:09:46,340
for your career.

126
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:52,260
Because of gratitude.

127
00:09:53,980 --> 00:09:54,700
Gratitude?

128
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,860
I was from a humble family.

129
00:10:01,820 --> 00:10:03,660
I’m not as talented as Su Shunqin

130
00:10:03,660 --> 00:10:04,780
or Ouyang Xiu.

131
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:07,180
They’ve been mean to me.

132
00:10:07,340 --> 00:10:08,300
That’s fine.

133
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:10,860
But my wife

134
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:13,020
married me

135
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:13,820
after her sister died of illness.

136
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,860
She was even mocked by other ladies

137
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:19,460
because of a poem Ouyang Xiu wrote.

138
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:23,260
But in the banquet that year,

139
00:10:25,020 --> 00:10:27,260
Noble Consort Zhang talked with my wife willingly

140
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:28,820
and saved her from embarrassment.

141
00:10:30,460 --> 00:10:31,580
Over the past years,

142
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:35,340
Noble Consort also made friends
with my wife sincerely.

143
00:10:39,580 --> 00:10:42,300
You’re an emotional man.

144
00:10:43,660 --> 00:10:44,980
More than gratitude.

145
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:49,420
I admire her.

146
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:52,620
Admire?

147
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:01,500
I admire her for her resolution, persistence,

148
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:03,940
enthusiasm and bravery.

149
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:08,500
That’s rare in the world.

150
00:11:10,180 --> 00:11:11,260
I fail to live a life like that.

151
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:14,300
So, I’d like to strive for something

152
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:16,620
that she didn’t have when she was alive.

153
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:21,980
Even at the price of

154
00:11:21,980 --> 00:11:22,820
ruining your career?

155
00:11:35,140 --> 00:11:36,860
I often make mistakes.

156
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:39,820
When it’s time to make a choice,

157
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:43,380
it doesn’t matter to do it again.

158
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,140
Huaiji.

159
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:18,300
Come over.

160
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:20,420
Princess.

161
00:12:20,860 --> 00:12:21,940
I don’t call you here,

162
00:12:21,940 --> 00:12:22,980
for playing together.

163
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:28,740
I’ve been composing a poem lately,

164
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:30,460
but I always fail.

165
00:12:40,980 --> 00:12:41,940
What do you mean?

166
00:12:42,860 --> 00:12:43,500
Oh,

167
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:46,620
look at it in the sun.

168
00:13:31,580 --> 00:13:32,420
Huaiji.

169
00:13:34,860 --> 00:13:35,940
You’re angry?

170
00:13:37,220 --> 00:13:38,060
Princess.

171
00:13:43,860 --> 00:13:44,660
Brother.

172
00:13:45,140 --> 00:13:46,420
You’re really angry with me?

173
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:47,700
Princess,

174
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:48,900
don’t call me like that anymore.

175
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,020
It makes me scared.

176
00:13:56,780 --> 00:13:57,900
Didn’t we make a deal that

177
00:13:58,020 --> 00:13:58,860
I could call you brother

178
00:13:58,860 --> 00:14:00,100
when no one was around?

179
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:09,260
Huaiji.

180
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:13,100
You’re angry with me.

181
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:18,860
You think I’m unruly

182
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:20,460
or even shameless?

183
00:14:22,620 --> 00:14:24,140
I wanted to listen to you.

184
00:14:25,540 --> 00:14:26,700
But look at father.

185
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:29,140
He also ignored etiquettes

186
00:14:29,420 --> 00:14:30,380
for Noble Consort Zhang,

187
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:32,980
I mean, Empress Zhang.

188
00:14:37,380 --> 00:14:38,100
Huaiji.

189
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:40,340
Don’t be angry with me.

190
00:14:40,660 --> 00:14:41,700
Don’t stop liking me.

191
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:42,780
You mustn’t!

192
00:14:49,940 --> 00:14:53,460
If you...

193
00:14:56,820 --> 00:14:58,580
you don’t allow me.

194
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:01,580
If you don’t like me to do that,

195
00:15:02,620 --> 00:15:03,380
I...

196
00:15:04,940 --> 00:15:09,140
I can probably ignore him,

197
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:16,580
though I like him.

198
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:21,580
Whenever I think of Li Wei

199
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:24,220
and his mother

200
00:15:24,220 --> 00:15:25,700
who I don’t even want to take a second look at.

201
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:29,460
I...

202
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:32,260
I would rather die right away.

203
00:15:35,220 --> 00:15:36,380
I’m not convinced.

204
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:40,580
I want to be happier.

205
00:15:44,420 --> 00:15:45,300
Huaiji.

206
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,380
If you don’t allow me,

207
00:15:50,860 --> 00:15:52,340
If you don’t like me to do that,

208
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:53,300
I...

209
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,100
No.

210
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:00,860
I don’t dare.

211
00:16:02,740 --> 00:16:03,460
And I won’t.

212
00:16:07,660 --> 00:16:09,660
Well, I’ll overstep my authority

213
00:16:10,940 --> 00:16:14,220
and let you call me brother.

214
00:16:16,220 --> 00:16:17,180
What kind of brother

215
00:16:18,140 --> 00:16:19,580
will not like his sister?

216
00:16:22,340 --> 00:16:23,900
Whatever kind of girl you are,

217
00:16:25,020 --> 00:16:26,700
I like that.

218
00:16:28,460 --> 00:16:29,900
I’ll always like you.

219
00:16:31,260 --> 00:16:32,860
I only adore girls like you.

220
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:39,700
Really?

221
00:16:42,180 --> 00:16:43,580
Why are you crying?

222
00:16:50,420 --> 00:16:51,340
I’m not crying.

223
00:16:53,260 --> 00:16:55,900
I read Mr. Cao Ping’s poem

224
00:16:56,340 --> 00:16:57,620
in the sun

225
00:16:59,420 --> 00:17:00,300
for a long time

226
00:17:00,860 --> 00:17:02,300
and my eyes sting.

227
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:06,500
Really?

228
00:17:08,860 --> 00:17:10,660
I never dare to lie to you.

229
00:17:19,740 --> 00:17:22,860
You wrote a nice poem.

230
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:26,540
I read it again and again,

231
00:17:28,020 --> 00:17:30,420
and I felt it wonderful.

232
00:17:33,340 --> 00:17:35,860
You just want to make me happy. Sounds insincere.

233
00:17:46,420 --> 00:17:48,220
Why are you staring at me like that?

234
00:17:53,820 --> 00:17:55,580
Anything on my face?

235
00:18:24,620 --> 00:18:27,420
Maybe I’ve written

236
00:18:27,420 --> 00:18:28,900
a terrible poem.

237
00:18:31,700 --> 00:18:32,620
A poem with true feelings

238
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:36,260
reads much better

239
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:37,860
than the homework

240
00:18:37,860 --> 00:18:38,820
His Majesty gave you.

241
00:18:41,940 --> 00:18:43,500
Let’s continue, then.

242
00:18:55,780 --> 00:19:01,780
= Hope I’ll... =

243
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:19,940
= Hope I’ll only have lovesickness in my heart =
But...

244
00:19:21,420 --> 00:19:22,700
But...

245
00:19:24,020 --> 00:19:26,740
If you think lovesickness is too frank,

246
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,860
we can change it into the grief of parting.

247
00:19:31,220 --> 00:19:32,180
Why?

248
00:19:32,860 --> 00:19:34,460
I didn’t say I would use the poem.

249
00:19:36,020 --> 00:19:37,540
I just wrote it for fun.

250
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:39,460
I didn’t mean to show it to anyone.

251
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:13,300
I’ll leave it here.

252
00:20:17,180 --> 00:20:17,860
It will be

253
00:20:20,380 --> 00:20:21,380
no longer needed.

254
00:20:30,340 --> 00:20:31,180
Done, Your Majesty.

255
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:34,140
Father.

256
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:37,500
Huirou.

257
00:20:41,380 --> 00:20:42,500
Today, I’m going to

258
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:45,060
Directorate of Education outside
the Rosefinch Gate.

259
00:20:45,140 --> 00:20:46,220
I’m leaving now.

260
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:48,060
What would you like?

261
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:48,940
I’ll bring it to you.

262
00:20:49,820 --> 00:20:50,980
I don’t want anything.

263
00:20:51,260 --> 00:20:52,380
I want you to take me with you

264
00:20:52,380 --> 00:20:53,380
for some lectures.

265
00:20:54,060 --> 00:20:54,860
No way.

266
00:20:55,380 --> 00:20:57,100
That never happened before.

267
00:20:58,580 --> 00:20:59,540
When Her Highness was young,

268
00:20:59,540 --> 00:21:01,140
she went to the academy, disguised as a boy.

269
00:21:01,860 --> 00:21:03,740
You always ask me to learn from Her Highness.

270
00:21:04,260 --> 00:21:05,940
Why don’t you let me experience more?

271
00:21:09,060 --> 00:21:10,100
Besides,

272
00:21:11,260 --> 00:21:13,100
for things that never happened before,

273
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:15,460
you just did one, didn’t you?

274
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:20,580
Father.

275
00:21:21,860 --> 00:21:22,980
During your trip,

276
00:21:23,260 --> 00:21:24,500
wherever you to,

277
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:25,940
your carriage is covered by curtains.

278
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:28,220
Wherever you stay for a rest,

279
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:30,420
there are screens and draperies.

280
00:21:31,140 --> 00:21:32,060
When I stay inside,

281
00:21:32,340 --> 00:21:33,460
no one will see me.

282
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:35,540
During the lectures,

283
00:21:35,780 --> 00:21:37,260
I’ll sit behind the screen

284
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:38,420
